  "description": "<h2> Electrical Specialist (Manufacturing)</h2><ul><li><p><strong>Up to $5,800++ gross monthly</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Basic salary up to $4,000</strong> (4-day work week option available)</p></li><li><p><strong>Daily shift & transport allowances</strong> (can exceed $300/month)</p></li><li><p><strong>Overtime pay</strong>, <strong>13th month salary</strong>, and <strong>performance bonus (1–2 months)</strong></p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Choose <strong>4, 5, or 6-day work weeks</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Rotating shifts</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Free shuttle bus</strong> from <strong>Choa Chu Kang</strong> & <strong>Joo Koon MRT</strong> to <strong>Tuas</strong></p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Keep electrical equipment running at peak performance</p></li><li><p>Troubleshoot and repair faults to minimize downtime</p></li><li><p>Execute preventive maintenance to avoid breakdowns</p></li><li><p>Support electrical upgrades and improvement projects</p></li><li><p>Ensure safety, compliance, and proper workplace organization</p></li><li><p>Work closely with production teams to boost efficiency</p></li><li><p>Guide and train operators and junior technicians</p></li></ul><ul><li><p><strong>NITEC / Higher NITEC / Diploma</strong> in Electrical Engineering or related field</p></li><li><p>Hands-on experience in a <strong>manufacturing or industrial environment</strong></p></li><li><p>Comfortable using <strong>electrical tools</strong> (multimeter, megger, thermal scanner)</p></li><li><p>Able to read <strong>electrical drawings and schematics</strong></p></li><li><p>Strong knowledge of <strong>motor controls, wiring, and automated lines</strong></p></li><li><p>Team player with clear communication skills</p></li><li><p>Willing to work <strong>rotating shifts</strong></p></li></ul><ul><li><p>PLC knowledge (Siemens, Allen Bradley)</p></li><li><p>Licensed Electrical Worker (LEW) certification</p></li></ul><p><br /><br /></p><p>EA Personnel R22110043 Tan Eng 